[[Image:Bust Grigore Ghica III Ia<U+015F>i Karl Storck.jpg|thumb|right|Bust of [[Grigore III Ghica|Grigore III Ghica of Moldavia]], in [[Ia<U+0219>i]]]]
[[Image:Palatul Sutu 2.jpg|thumb|right|The [[<U+015E>u<U+0163>u Palace]] in Bucharest]]
'''Karl Storck'''  was a [[Grand Duchy of Hesse|Hessian]]-born [[Romania]]n sculptor and art theorist.

==Biography==
Karl Storck was born on in [[Hanau]], [[Grand Duchy of Hesse]].<ref>Turner, p.721</ref> Having been trained and working for a time as an engraver, he became sculptor only later.<ref>Turner, p.721</ref> He studied in [[Paris]], from where he was driven out by the [[French Revolution of 1848]].<ref>Turner, p.721</ref> He settled in [[Bucharest]] in 1849, and spent the years 1856-1857 in [[Munich]] where he trained as sculptor. In 1865 he became the first professor of sculpture at the [[Fine Arts Academy]] in Bucharest, becoming the most prominent figure and main developer in this early period of modern [[Romanian sculpture]]<ref>Daicoviciu, p.123</ref><ref>Keefe, p.98</ref>

His sons, [[Carol Storck]] (1854 - 1926) and [[Frederic Storck]] (1872 - 1924), were also noted artists.

==Notable pupils==
* [[Ion Georgescu]]
* [[Paul Focs<U+0103>neanu]]
* [[George Julian Zolnay]]

==List of works==
* ''Domni<U+0163>a B<U+0103>la<U+015F>a'', ''Sp<U+0103>tarul Mihail Cantacuzino'', ''Ana Davila''
* Bust of [[Grigore III Ghica|Grigore III Ghica of Moldavia]], in [[Ia<U+0219>i]]
* ''[[Minerva]] <U+00EE>ncunun<U+00E2>nd artele <U+0219>i <U+0219>tiin<U+021B>a''
* The [[iconostasis]] of [[Viforata Monastery]] (15th century)
* Bas-reliefs on the facade of the [[University of Bucharest]] (destroyed by the [[Bombing of Bucharest in World War II|Allied bombing of Bucharest]])
* Facade and interior of the [[<U+015E>u<U+0163>u Palace]]
<small>Portraits</small>
* Busts of [[Theodor Aman]], [[Alexandru Ioan Cuza]], [[Mihail Kog<U+0103>lniceanu]], [[C. A. Rosetti]], [[Elena Cuza]]

